ğŸ”¹ What is the Grid System?

Bootstrapâ€™s grid system uses a 12-column layout to create responsive page structures.
You divide your layout using rows and columns.

ğŸ’¡ Structure
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col">Column 1</div>
    <div class="col">Column 2</div>
    <div class="col">Column 3</div>
  </div>
</div>


Each .col divides the row equally into parts that sum up to 12.

ğŸ“˜ Fixed Column Widths Example
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-4 bg-primary text-white p-3">col-4</div>
    <div class="col-8 bg-success text-white p-3">col-8</div>
  </div>
</div>


âœ… Total = 4 + 8 = 12 columns (full width)

ğŸ“± Responsive Columns Example
<div class="container text-center">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm-4 col-md-3 bg-info p-3">Left</div>
    <div class="col-sm-8 col-md-9 bg-warning p-3">Right</div>
  </div>
</div>


ğŸª„ This adjusts automatically:

On small screens â†’ 4:8 ratio

On medium and larger â†’ 3:9 ratio

âš™ï¸ Breakpoints in Bootstrap Grid
Breakpoint	Class Prefix	Screen Size
Extra small	.col-	<576px
Small	.col-sm-	â‰¥576px
Medium	.col-md-	â‰¥768px
Large	.col-lg-	â‰¥992px
Extra large	.col-xl-	â‰¥1200px
XXL	.col-xxl-	â‰¥1400px
ğŸ’¡ Nested Grids Example
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-8 bg-light border">
      Parent Col
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-6 bg-secondary text-white p-2">Nested Col 1</div>
        <div class="col-6 bg-dark text-white p-2">Nested Col 2</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-4 bg-info text-white p-3">Parent Col 2</div>
  </div>
</div>






